http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14115440/pygame-installation-for-python-3-3
link explains more

install python 3.3.0 win 32 bit from here
https://www.python.org/download/releases/3.3.0/

install pygame 
pygame-1.9.2a0.win32-py3.3.msi
from here
https://bitbucket.org/pygame/pygame/downloads

your python install and pygame MUST BOTH BE 32 bit, pygame doesn't have a 64 bit vs
i just made sure they were the same version for good measure since python's latest is only like 3.4

The zip file in the repository contains a bunch of examples of different things you can do with pygame, take a look

Here are Links to tutorials i showed you which seemed pretty simple to me, and a good basis for what we will have to use
http://inventwithpython.com/chapter17.html
http://inventwithpython.com/chapter18.html
Book is from pygame's tutorial section, and is pretty easy to read
